# CardOrbit Web Consumer Design System (active)

Authority: `docs/design/WEB_CONSUMER_DESIGN_SYSTEM.md`

## Theme & vibe

- **Fonts:** Geist (display + body) via `consumer-theme.css` / deferred CDN; Inter fallback
- **Chrome:** Deep Space dark glass (`.site-header`, `.consumer-footer`, `.consumer-surface--glass`)
- **Hero / auth rail:** dark ambient panels; light text; blue→purple gradient CTAs
- **Brand:** `HeroLogo` only (`@brand/HeroLogo`); favicon uses orbital `HeroLogoMark`
- **User-facing name:** CardOrbit (do not rename `@cardwise/*` packages, APIs, folders, env vars)

## Palette (locked)

- Deep Space `#050816`, Secondary `#0B1023`, Surface `#111827`, Elevated `#161D33`
- Primary `#4F8CFF`, Orbit Purple `#7C5CFF`
- Border `rgba(255,255,255,0.08)`

## Components

- Reuse `@brand`, `@marketing`, `@layout`, `@motion` — no duplicate logo or card components
- **Auth:** generic `AnimatedCardStack` (no issuer photos)
- **Landing:** `variant="showcase"` + `RecommendationPreview`
- Links: `consumerLink` from `@lib/consumer-link`
- Route scroll: `ScrollToTop` already in `App.tsx`

## New pages

- Wrap in `AppShell` patterns; use `.consumer-surface` for panels
- Set `document.title` to `CardOrbit · …` per route
- One `h1` per page; semantic heading order

## Milestone verification (web changes)

When editing `apps/web`, run before final review:

```bash
bun run verify:web
```

Lighthouse: Accessibility/Best Practices/SEO ≥90 enforced; Performance target ≥85 (advisory until M-085).

Do not introduce alternate color systems or fonts without plan/ADR update.
